<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-12T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-12T02:00:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/649: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gwynn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-12T09:00:00+02:00">September
                                    12, 1942—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 11:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>340. My 317, August 31, 9 a.m. Syrian <hi rend="italic">Official
                                Journal</hi> September 3 publishes a decree of August 25 the
                            substance of which reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The hospital of the American Mission in Syria located at Deir ez
                                    Zor is exempted for all direct taxes as of the date of its
                                    establishment. All taxes paid by this hospital will be returned
                                    to it.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>It will be noted that the terms of the decree are much less comprehensive
                            than those of the note dated August 24. This latter in turn would appear
                            to me scarcely to satisfy the request contained in the informal <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> I left with the Syrian Foreign
                            Minister on August 20.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gwynn</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>